Vice Chairman, Board of Directors

                    Current                  


YMCA of Greenwich

                    This Y, registered in the National Historicregistry, is one of the focal points of the community and has remainedstrong for many years, filling an important role in this town, enriching thewhole person; body, mind and spirit through innovative programs, services andmost importantly personalized relationships.  Currently completing animmense full renovation to the original building and the addition of an Olympicsize pool now home to #1 rank YMCA Dive team, Olympic Junior Gold Water PoloGirls team, and both state and national record holding youth and adultswimmers.  The Greenwich Family Y welcomes everyone to participateregardless of their gender, race, religion, ethnicity or skill level. No one isturned away for inability to pay. Our volunteer board sets policy for ourPresident and CEO, Rebecca Fretty, who manages the operation withfull-time and part-time staff and volunteer leaders. YMCA programs are toolsfor building the values of caring, honesty, respect and responsibility.                  





